    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl> <ptr target="#oliverioTacc"/> <citedRange>VIII.9</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>142</citedRange> (drawing)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>099100</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Σώπατρος"><supplied reason="lost">Σώπ</supplied>ατρος</name> 
                        <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-66134"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Χαῖνυς">Χαίνυος</name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><space quantity="5" unit="character"/> <w lemma="δεκάτα">δεκάταν</w> <space quantity="5" unit="character"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1">
                        <lem><supplied reason="lost">Σώπ</supplied>ατρος</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><unclear>α</unclear>τρος</rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="2">
                        <lem><space quantity="5" unit="character"/> δεκάταν <space quantity="5" unit="character"/></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> δεκάταν</rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Sopatros fils de Khainus <supplied reason="subaudible">a consacré ce monument</supplied> au titre de la dîme.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Sopatros son of Chainys <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated this monument</supplied> as a tithe.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Sopatros figlio di Chainys <supplied reason="subaudible">ha dedicato questo monumento</supplied> come decima.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Pugliese Carratelli could not find the stone in 1960 and published this inscription from a drawing in Oliverio's papers.</p>
                <p>The stone, being complete at left back, allows to restore 3 letters at the beginning of line 1; in the repertory of Cyrenaean names, 
                    <foreign xml:lang="grc">Σώπατρος</foreign> is the only name matching the gap. Although the father's name is rather rare at Cyrene, it would be hazardous 
                to restore the same first name also at <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr099000</ref>.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
